  "backdrop": "caves",
  "story": {
    "intro": [
      "The sky-wyrm Ouln has swallowed the harvest moon, and with it the last of the light.",
      "You pilot the Splinter, a needle-ship small enough to fly straight down its throat.",
      "Thread the living gullet. Where the walls close, be thinner. Where they part, be faster."
    ],
    "levelIntros": [
      "THE OPEN THROAT: The gullet is wide here, but it is not empty. Gut-mites taste the newcomer.",
      "THE NARROWS: The walls pulse tight. Turrets of bone track the trench. Weave, do not stop.",
      "THE HEARTPIT: Past the last ring of teeth, the wyrm's stolen heart beats behind its guard."
    ],
    "bossIntro": "OULN'S MAW turns inward at last - a hive of teeth grown around the swallowed moon. Cut it out.",
    "victory": [
      "The heart bursts and the moon rolls free, spilling silver back up the throat like a tide.",
      "The Splinter rides the light out into open sky. Below, a wyrm learns to be hungry elsewhere."
    ],
    "defeat": [
      "The gullet closes. The Splinter is one more bright thing the dark will slowly forget. Again.",
      "Ouln swallows and sleeps. But needles do not dissolve, and this one still has a point. Again."
    ]
  },
